      "markdown": "# üì¢ B12 ‚Äî Imperatives + Pronoun Placement (B1)\n\n**Goal:** Give commands and instructions with correct pronoun use.\n\n---\n\n## ‚úÖ Affirmative Imperatives\n\n| Person | -AR (*hablar*) | -ER (*comer*) | -IR (*vivir*) |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| t√∫ | habla | come | vive |\n| vosotros/as | hablad | comed | vivid |\n| usted | hable | coma | viva |\n| ustedes | hablen | coman | vivan |\n\n> Formed from the present tense without the subject pronoun.\n\n### Irregular **t√∫** forms\n\n| Verb | Command |\n| --- | --- |\n| venir | ven |\n| decir | di |\n| salir | sal |\n| hacer | haz |\n| tener | ten |\n| ir | ve |\n| poner | pon |\n| ser | s√© |\n\n---\n\n## üö´ Negative Imperatives\n\nUse the **present subjunctive** pattern.\n\n| Person | -AR (*hablar*) | -ER (*comer*) | -IR (*vivir*) |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| t√∫ | no hables | no comas | no vivas |\n| vosotros/as | no habl√©is | no com√°is | no viv√°is |\n| usted | no hable | no coma | no viva |\n| ustedes | no hablen | no coman | no vivan |\n\n---\n\n## ‚ö° Pronoun Placement\n\n| Context | Placement | Example |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Affirmative command | Attach to the end | *D√≠melo.*, *Lev√°ntate.* |\n| Negative command | Before the verb | *No me lo digas.*, *No te levantes.* |\n| Infinitive / gerund combos | Attach to the end | *Quiero dec√≠rtelo.*, *Est√° explic√°ndoselo.* |\n\n> ‚úèÔ∏è Add an accent when attaching two pronouns: *d√≠melo, c√≥metelo*.\n\n---\n\n> üìù Summary: Affirmative imperatives attach pronouns; negative commands place pronouns before the verb, all based on present tense/subjunctive patterns.",
      "references": []
    }
  ],
